Police are investigating the death of a 17-year-old girl whose body was found after a house party.

The teenager was discovered by a friend at 9am on Friday.

Officers said the death was being treated as 'unexplained' and a post mortem examination would be held to determine the cause of death. 

One neighbour in the village of Ditchling, East Sussex, who asked not to be named, said: 'It is normally such a quiet village – you do not expect this sort of thing to happen. It is absolutely tragic.'

