Others said they believed the girl attended a secondary school in nearby Lewes.

Yesterday police officers stood guard outside the property and the road was closed for a number of hours as police launched an investigation into the death  

Detective Chief Inspector Mark O'Brien said: 'This is a tragic incident and our thoughts are with the girl's family and friends at this sad time.

'A post-mortem will be held to determine the cause of her death, but until that time it will be treated as unexplained.'

 

